Real GNSS data fixtures
=======================

These files are genuine GNSS data, included so the parsers and the positioning
solver are validated against real broadcast/precise products rather than only
self-authored samples (see tests/igs_real_data.rs and tests/pvt_abmf.rs). They
are not part of the Kshana source and are not shipped in the published
crates/packages — they exist only for the test suite.

ABMF00GLP_R_20181330000_01D_30S_MO.rnx
  A RINEX 3.02 multi-GNSS observation excerpt from IGS station ABMF (Aubergine,
  Le Moule, Guadeloupe; a Septentrio PolarX5 / Trimble antenna), 2018-05-13
  (day 133) starting 01:30:00 GPS, two epochs, eleven GPS satellites with L1/L2
  code. Used by tests/pvt_abmf.rs to validate single-point positioning against
  the station's surveyed coordinate. The station's published ITRF/IGS a-priori
  position is carried in the file's APPROX POSITION XYZ header record
  (2919786.4480, -5383745.1780, 1774604.7340 m). Obtained from the georinex test
  corpus (below).

BRDC00WRD_R_20181330000_01D_GN.rnx
  The GPS broadcast navigation (ephemeris) for 2018-05-13, the IGS/BKG combined
  BRDC product (BKG Frankfurt), trimmed to the GPS records with reference times
  00:00 and 02:00 that bracket the ABMF observation epoch. Paired with the ABMF
  observation file for the positioning validation. GNSS broadcast ephemerides are
  open data distributed by the IGS; obtained from
  https://igs.bkg.bund.de (IGS/BKG, open data).

BRDM00DLR_R_20130010000_01D_MN.rnx
  A RINEX 3.02 mixed (multi-GNSS) broadcast navigation file for 2013-01-01,
  produced by the DLR/TUM CONGO + IGS MGEX tracking effort
  (O. Montenbruck, DLR; P. Steigenberger, TUM). GNSS broadcast ephemerides are
  open data distributed by the International GNSS Service (IGS).

igs_sample.sp3
  A RINEX/SP3-c precise-orbit excerpt for 2017-02-14 (IGS14 frame), the first
  epoch of an IGS combined orbit product. The second epoch is truncated; the
  file exercises the SP3 reader. IGS products are openly available.

The ABMF observation excerpt, the 2013 DLR/TUM navigation file, and the SP3
excerpt were obtained from the test corpus of the georinex project
(https://github.com/geospace-code/georinex, BSD-3-Clause, M. Hirsch), which
redistributes them for testing. The 2018 GPS broadcast navigation was obtained
from the open IGS/BKG archive (https://igs.bkg.bund.de). The underlying data are
the property of, and courtesy of, the IGS and the contributing analysis centres
(DLR/TUM, BKG). See https://igs.org for the IGS data and product use terms.
